  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a bowl, mix together all the dry ingredients (your cornflour and various seasonings) apart from the desiccated coconut and chilli flakes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add desiccated coconut and milk into two separate bowls."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the paneer into 25 cubes. Take each cube, dip into the milk, then into the dry cornflour mixture, back into the milk, and finally into the desiccated coconut."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once all 25 pieces have been coated, heat up your coconut oil in a non-stick pan on a medium-high heat and cook for a few mins on each side until crispy."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now it’s time to make your honey. Start by finely dicing your chilli. Wipe down the pan and add the diced chilli along with your chilli flakes. Cook this on a dry pan on low heat for 1 minute. Then add in the honey and squeeze in the juice of a lime. Mix to combine and cook this for 4 mins, to allow the chillies to infuse in the honey. This will be very hot, so carefully pour into a small dish and leave to cool."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, dip the paneer in the hot honey and enjoy."
    }
  ],
